## 📖 Reading Order Recommendations

### For Students Starting from Scratch

```
1. COMPLETE_PACKAGING_GUIDE.md (Quick Start section)
   ↓ (Understand overall structure)
2. PROJECT_REQUIREMENTS.md (Read your specific project section)
   ↓ (Know the requirements)
3. DIRECTORY_STRUCTURE.md (Canonical layout section)
   ↓ (Organize your files)
4. FILE_INVENTORY.md (Create your tracking sheet)
   ↓ (Start tracking progress)
5. Begin development!
```

### For Students with Existing Projects

```
1. DIRECTORY_STRUCTURE.md (Current vs Canonical section)
   ↓ (Check if reorganization needed)
2. FILE_INVENTORY.md (Fill in current status)
   ↓ (Identify missing files)
3. COMPLETE_PACKAGING_GUIDE.md (Workflow section)
   ↓ (Follow best practices going forward)
4. PROJECT_REQUIREMENTS.md (Reference as needed)
   ↓ (Verify each requirement)
```

### For Students Ready to Deploy

```
1. FILE_INVENTORY.md (Submission Checklist)
   ↓ (Verify everything complete)
2. COMPLETE_PACKAGING_GUIDE.md (Quality Assurance section)
   ↓ (Run validation checks)
3. AUTOMATION_GUIDE.md (Deployment section)
   ↓ (Choose your deployment method)
4. Deploy and verify on live server
```

